About Buoy Health: 
Buoy builds a digital health tool that helps people â€“ from the moment they get sick â€“ start their health care on the right foot. Started by a team of doctors and computer scientists working at the Harvard Innovation Laboratory in Boston MA, Buoy was developed in direct response to the downward spiral weâ€™ve all faced when we attempt to self-diagnose our symptoms online. Buoy leverages artificial intelligence â€“ powered by advanced machine learning and proprietary granular data - to resemble an exchange you would have with your favorite doctor â€“ to provide consumers with a real-time, accurate analysis of their symptoms and help them easily and quickly embark on the right path to getting better. Buoy is based in Boston and was founded in 2014. 
About the role: 
The VP of Finance will join as a key executive during an exciting time in Buoyâ€™s growth story post a Fall 2020 Series C. This role will bring challenging dynamic responsibilities that drive your professional development and career growth. The VP of Finance will be charged with building the infrastructure surrounding all things financial operations and supporting broader business model growth decisions. This individual will be responsible for driving capital efficiency while managing financial operations such as budgeting, forecasting, FP&A, and reporting. They will partner cross-functionally, using metrics and processes in the pursuit of meeting growth milestones and addressing challenges. They should love solving complex business problems and thrive in a fast-paced environment. 
The ideal candidate is highly self-motivated and possesses a stellar work ethic. The VP of Finance will report to the CEO. The VP of Finance will also operate on the executive team, partnering with the CEO and Board of Directors to chart a path of ambitious growth for Buoy. 
Responsibilities:
 - Partner and work collaboratively as a trusted advisor with the executive leadership team on initiatives, including budgeting, reporting, and operational models 
- Assess, evaluate and recommend changes based on the financial performance of the organization 
- Lead communication and reporting to the Board of Directors on business and financial performance 
- Develop and maintain key banking and investor relationships 
- Ensure that processes and infrastructure are rigorous and support the company's growth strategically; continuously improve the efficiency of operations 
- Provide financial analysis and business support in evaluation of new business endeavors, special projects, hiring plans, and other initiatives 
- Lead decision making around unit economics, pricing, and key contracts 
- Provide financial support and expertise throughout the company including cash flow analysis, variance reporting, short-term and long-term range profitability analysis and financial projections 
- Build and maintain the annual operating plan and monthly operating budgets 
- Build and maintain the 5 year long-range model 
- Help lead the company through future fundraising and transaction efforts 
- Establish key performance metrics to keep the company aligned and executing on tasks; provide all key business unit leaders with accurate, timely and relevant financial reporting against metrics and results. 
- Lead financial planning and analysis to provide strategic recommendations to continuously improve company operating efficiencies 
- Oversee the company's accounting function, including revenue management, payables, A/R and collections, and taxes 
- Ensure all regulatory and compliance business requirements are fulfilled 
- Oversee any/all audit operations and manage external accounting firm 
- Manage outsourced accounting firm and internal finance team 
About you: 
- 10+ years in progressive finance roles (pre-IPO experience preferred) 
- MBA and/or CPA preferred 
- Software, SaaS or managed marketplace experience a plus 
- Investor relations and treasury management experience a plus 
- Highly analytical skills with a strong eye for business and the ability to cross between the strategic and the detail. 
- Background in corporate finance, venture-backed startups, M&A, or other high-growth, entrepreneurial environments is a HUGE plus 
- Shown ability to lead and motivate teams: achieving organizational focus on key priorities, providing clear direction, delegating, actively communicating and coaching 
- Outstanding communication and presentation skills 
- Mission-driven and self-motivated 
- Grace under pressure, and a sense of humor 
- A high-energy and strategic leader, capable of operating at speed, seeing around corners and instilling discipline throughout the organization 
- World-class problem-solver - knows when to get in the weeds and when to zoom out to 10,000 feet. Has an intuitive sense for what the right answer is, informed by pattern recognition and sound judgment 
- Collaborative and team-oriented, with an inclusive and hands-on leadership style. Knows when to lead from the front, when to take a backseat, and when to disagree and commit 
Benefits: 
- Stock Options 
- Unlimited PTO 
- Medical, Dental, Vision 
- 401k with matching 
- Dogs in the office! 
- Work from wherever 
 
